open JDK Java should be installed.
verify java installation "java -version".

Then visit 'https://updates.jenkins-ci.org/download/war/' to download a particular version by uing a wget command.
$ wget https://get.jenkins.io/war-stable/2.426.3/jenkins.war
$ wget https://updates.jenkins-ci.org/download/war/2.162/jenkins.war

$ java -jar jenkins.war ( default runs on 8080 port )

$ java -jar jenkins.war --httpPort=5000 ( if you want run on any other port use this, in my case its 5000 port )

$ nohup java -jar jenkins.jar & ( to run jenkins process in background )
